<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="925" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d925">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.55/10</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LM1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Langhorne</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-20T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>444. Your 760, March 10, 11 a.m. Is communication with <persName corresp="#p_WB1">Whitlock</persName> cut off both by mail and
                            telegraph? If so, when will it be reestablished? Can you explain
                            statement that he has no funds? Keep Department fully informed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>